# 🎯 Main Objective: Create a Case Study Document

- [ ] 1. Initialize case study file
  - [ ] 1.1. Create markdown file in case-studies directory
    ```markdown
    # [Project Name] Case Study
    ```
  - [ ] 1.2. Add required metadata
    ```markdown
    ---
    title: Project Name
    type: client|technical|process|innovation
    industry: Industry Name
    duration: X months
    audience: Developers|Clients|Internal
    platforms: Website|LinkedIn|Blog
    ---
    ```

- [ ] 2. Document core sections
  - [ ] 2.1. Write executive summary
    ```markdown
    ## 🎯 Executive Summary
    - Achievement: [Key metric]
    - Timeline: [Duration]
    - Impact: [Business value]
    ```
  - [ ] 2.2. Describe challenge and solution
    ```markdown
    ## 🔍 Challenge
    - Initial problem
    - Business impact
    - Technical constraints

    ## 💡 Solution
    - Approach taken
    - Key technologies
    - Architecture overview
    ```
  - [ ] 2.3. Add implementation details
    ```markdown
    ## ⚙️ Implementation
    - Step 1: [Action]
    - Step 2: [Action]
    
    ### Code Example
    ```code
    // Key implementation detail
    ```
    ```

- [ ] 3. Add supporting content
  - [ ] 3.1. Insert media assets
    ```markdown
    ![Description](./images/screenshot.png)
    ```
  - [ ] 3.2. Include metrics and results
    ```markdown
    ## 📊 Results
    - Metric 1: [Value]
    - Metric 2: [Value]
    - ROI: [Calculation]
    ```
  - [ ] 3.3. Add testimonials
    ```markdown
    ## 👥 Testimonials
    > "Quote from stakeholder" - Name, Role
    ```

- [ ] 4. Review and publish
  - [ ] 4.1. Verify content accuracy
  - [ ] 4.2. Get stakeholder approval
  - [ ] 4.3. Create platform-specific versions
  - [ ] 4.4. Publish to designated platforms
